post: {'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will decrease the number of fatal overdoses by giving each user a safe dose of the drugs by regulating the drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use will not cease regardless of the legal status. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even though illegal drugs may still exist if drugs were legalised, there would be far less of them than when illegal drugs were the only option. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine is [highly addictive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_dependence) and easy to become dependent on. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tobacco farming before abolition was [done by slaves](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_in_the_American_colonies). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking drugs can be a pleasurable experience.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One solution for recreational availability of such drugs could be to require that they emit an unmistakable coloring or odour/taste when dissolved in a drink.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A high level of correlation does not indicate which of the variables is the cause and which is the effect. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That correlation is not affected by their legality. So, legalization will not make it worse unless it causes the price to go down. Given the emphasis many put on drug taxes as an argument in favor of legalization, that seems unlikely.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This could lead individuals into a false sense of safety when it comes to drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would allow for a boom in the economy as there would be an increased demand, and so more farmers would be required to grow the drugs required.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Making it legal for companies to sell and market these drugs for recreational use without an understanding of the negative consequences that these substances cause is unethical. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalization \\(and incarceration\\) causes lasting harm to a person's health and life outcomes."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a high level of correlation between [poverty](https://borgenproject.org/addiction-poverty-connected/) and substance abuse.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs will lead to people having hallucinations or becoming violent. In these instances, individuals may be a danger to themselves or others. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There has been [no scientific consensus](https://newatlas.com/study-effects-ecstasy/10995/) on the long-term effects of ecstasy use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The effects of smoking are slow and not always visible; this means people are not as aware of them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will remove the taboo that drug addiction currently carries with it. As a result, addicts will no longer be a target of prejudice. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies might just as well synthesize new, less addictive and harmful drugs to meet the demand.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow access to drugs to be graded based on risks taking them, meaning more addictive and harmful drugs could be made less available and desirable by taxing them accordingly.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The syntheses for many illicit, addictive and recreational drugs is already known, there would be high amounts of money spent on R&D for new less addictive drugs. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Inappropriate recreational drug use has negative health consequences. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Making it legal for companies to sell and market these drugs for recreational use without an understanding of the negative consequences that these substances cause is unethical. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education and information might not be enough to ensure thoughtful drug use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Former inmates are significantly more at risk of drug-related mortality than the general population.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, obtaining such drugs is risky, restricted and requires work. Even if they're available, making them freely available may increase the number of rape incidents."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It would likely be 'cooler' because companies can market the drugs like they do with cigarettes and alcohol."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established companies would be strictly controlled.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The reason for black market chemicals to be cheaper, is that the black market doesn't care about cost incurring legal restrictions and taxes. I think drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
